annotationA: Coat protein (Coatomer) zeta, isoform A; Structural molecule activity; transporter activity; oxidoreductase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: phagocytosis; oxidation-reduction process; retrograde vesicle-mediated transport, Golgi to ER; regulation of lipid storage
annotationB: ER lumen protein-retaining receptor; Required for the retention of luminal endoplasmic reticulum proteins. Determines the specificity of the luminal ER protein retention system. Also required for normal vesicular traffic through the Golgi (By similarity)
